* Phase 2: Spring in OfficeFloor

  In this phase the OfficeFloor runtime takes ownership of the HTTP server while your existing Spring
  configuration continues to supply dependency-injected beans.  No Spring code changes are required.
  Moving to this phase unlocks further OfficeFloor capabilities — such as native thread injection
  and the full WoOF infrastructure layer — while the familiar Spring programming model remains intact.


** Spring Beans

  Host Spring beans directly as OfficeFloor managed objects.  Your Spring <<<@Service>>>,
  <<<@Repository>>>, and <<<@Component>>> beans are available for injection into any OfficeFloor
  procedure exactly as they are in a Spring Boot application.

*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
|| Tutorial                                                    || Description                                               || Covered
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./spring_officefloor/SpringHttpServer/index.html}Spring Beans}} | Host Spring beans inside the OfficeFloor runtime. Spring is used purely as a dependency supplier; all beans remain available for injection. | SpringSupplierSource\
|                                                              |                                                            | Spring beans as managed objects
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+


** Spring Web MVC in OfficeFloor

  Host an existing Spring Web MVC application inside the OfficeFloor runtime.  Existing
  <<<@Controller>>> endpoints continue to work; YAML REST procedures can be added alongside them.

*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
|| Tutorial                                                    || Description                                               || Covered
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./spring_officefloor/SpringWebMvcHttpServer/index.html}Spring Web MVC}} | Run Spring Web MVC @Controller endpoints within OfficeFloor while adding YAML REST procedures. | Spring Web MVC\
|                                                              |                                                            | @Controller in OfficeFloor
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+


** Spring Web Flux in OfficeFloor

  Host an existing Spring Web Flux application inside the OfficeFloor runtime.

*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
|| Tutorial                                                    || Description                                               || Covered
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
