** Infrastructure and Concurrency

  OfficeFloor's {{{https://sagenschneider.blogspot.com/2019/02/inversion-of-coupling-control.html}IOCC}}
  model provides fine-grained control over threads, start-up ordering, caching, and modularisation.
  These tutorials explore that infrastructure layer.

*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
|| Tutorial                                                    || Description                                               || Covered
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./native/infrastructure/TeamHttpServer/index.html}Thread Injection}} | Assign specific thread teams to procedures to performance-tune the application. | Thread Injection
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./native/infrastructure/ThreadAffinityHttpServer/index.html}Thread Affinity}} | Bind procedures to CPU cores using the Executive for cache-friendly execution. | Executive
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./native/infrastructure/StartBeforeHttpServer/index.html}Start-up Ordering}} | Declare ordered start-up dependencies between ManagedObjectSource instances. | start-before , start-after
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./native/infrastructure/ConstantCacheHttpServer/index.html}Cache}} | Cache constant values to avoid repeated computation or lookup. | {{{/apidocs/net/officefloor/cache/Cache.html}Cache}}
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./native/infrastructure/ActivityHttpServer/index.html}Activity}} | Modularise REST YAML configuration into reusable Activity units. | Activity (Section)
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./native/infrastructure/TestHttpServer/index.html}Testing}} | Unit, system, and integration test OfficeFloor REST applications. | Unit / System / Integration testing
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+


** Static Content

  For modern single-page applications, the REST YAML endpoints provide the API and static assets
  are served directly from the classpath.

*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
|| Tutorial                                                    || Description                                               || Covered
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./native/core/StaticContentHttpServer/index.html}Static Content}} | Serve SPA assets (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) from the <<<PUBLIC/>>> classpath directory alongside REST endpoints. | /PUBLIC
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+


* Phase 4: OfficeFloor Features

  Advanced capabilities available in the OfficeFloor runtime: integrating reactive streams and
  writing procedure logic in JVM languages other than Java.


** Reactive

  OfficeFloor's threading model integrates cleanly with reactive libraries.  These tutorials
  demonstrate how to wire reactive streams and reactive database clients as procedures in REST YAML
  composition.

*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
|| Tutorial                                                    || Description                                               || Covered
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/reactive/ReactorHttpServer/index.html}Reactor}} | Integrate Project Reactor publishers and subscribers as OfficeFloor procedures. | {{{https://projectreactor.io/}Project Reactor}}\
|                                                              |                                                            | Reactive streams
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/reactive/R2dbcHttpServer/index.html}R2DBC}}    | Reactive relational database access using R2DBC within OfficeFloor REST composition. | {{{https://r2dbc.io}R2DBC}}\
|                                                              |                                                            | Reactive database
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/reactive/VertxSqlClientHttpServer/index.html}Vertx SQL Client}} | High-performance database interaction using the Vert.x SQL Client. | {{{https://github.com/eclipse-vertx/vertx-sql-client}Vertx SQL Client}}
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+


** Polyglot

  OfficeFloor procedures can be written in any JVM language.  Mix Kotlin, Scala, or JavaScript
  logic into the same REST YAML endpoint graph as Java procedures.

*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
|| Tutorial                                                    || Description                                               || Covered
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/polyglot/KotlinHttpServer/index.html}Kotlin}}  | Implement REST procedure logic in Kotlin alongside Java procedures. | Polyglot Kotlin
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/polyglot/ScalaHttpServer/index.html}Scala}}    | Implement REST procedure logic in Scala alongside Java procedures. | Polyglot Scala
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/polyglot/JavaScriptHttpServer/index.html}JavaScript}} | Implement REST procedure logic in JavaScript via GraalVM. | Polyglot JavaScript\
|                                                              |                                                            | GraalVM
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/polyglot/CatsHttpServer/index.html}Cats Effect}} | Integrate Cats Effect functional IO into OfficeFloor REST composition. | {{{https://typelevel.org/cats-effect/}Cats Effect}}
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| {{{./features/polyglot/ZioHttpServer/index.html}ZIO}}        | Integrate ZIO functional effects into OfficeFloor REST composition. | {{{https://zio.dev}ZIO}}
*--------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------+


